body:
@varac How does this work with multiple alacritty instances? Surely toggling to light on one process will cause all other processes to toggle as well?

My particular use case is that I’d like to have an opacity = 0.8 normally, but when I enter vim I’d like the opacity to be 1.0. With IPC it would be possible to alias vim to some script which sends a message to alacritty and switches the opacity.

The colors inside vim itself isn’t actually an issue, but the padding pixels are still transparent in vim and I’d like to get rid of that.
